  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Community-based health and protection intervention for most at risk older people affected by the Beirut port explosion</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The aim of this programme is to imporve health and protection services for older people affected by the Bierut port explosion, in particular those living alone, older-women-headed households and older people with underlying health conditions or mobility impairment. The activities supporting this aim include: home-based medical consultations through outreach teams; home-based care by community volunteers (including Covid-safe practices); psycho-social counselling; in-clinic consultations where required and support to a hotline for mental health consultations. The work will be undetaken by local partners with support and overal programme management by HelpAge.</narrative>
  </description>
